Palindromic take a string and returns an array of the top three palindromes found in that string. If there are no palindromes in the string, it returns an error.

## Usage

findPalindromes.js has three main functions:

 * prepareString
 * findPalindromesInString
 * returnTopThreePalindromes.
 
```js
    var string = 'beeeeeeeb abbba xyz noon A man, a plan, a canal â€“ Panama!';
    var prepString = prepareString(string, false);
    var positionArray = findPalindromesInString(string, false);
           document.getElementById("string").innerHTML = prepString;
           document.getElementById("positionArray").innerHTML = posArray;
           document.getElementById("palindromes").innerHTML = returnTopThreePalindromes(prepString, posArray);
           
```